FBIS4-12625 "drnes069_d_94002" FBIS-NES-94-069 Daily Report 9 Apr 1994 Libya JANA: America Suffering From `Power-Mania' JANA: America Suffering From `Power-Mania' LD0904181094 Tripoli JANA in English 1805 GMT 9 Apr 94 LD0904181094 Tripoli JANA English BFN [Text] London, Al-Tayr [April] 9, JAMAHIRIYAH NEWS AGENCY -- The American assistant secretary of state for international security said in a press statement on Thursday that Iraq, Iran, Libya and North Korea must be prevented from obtaining some types of sensitive technology. America suffers from power-mania, practices a strange racial discrimination, deals with world resources and peoples' rights in a tragic manner and mankind are being threatened as a result of American behaviour.
